bio.p:
Susan Green(
   susanjgreen@bigpond.com
) is completing her dissertation in English literature at Macquarie University, Sydney, Australia. Her thesis is an interdisciplinary investigation into the representation of consciousness in the major novels of Virginia Woolf and Ian McEwan. Susan currently teaches the first-year unit: Approaches to English Literature, and co-teaches a third-year unit: Narrative and the Novel.
